Requirements:-
Embedded systems project
design and implement a lexical analyser for a C-langauge subset.
maximize speed and minimize space.
lexical analyser must apply in-depth knowledge of 'pointer arithemetic' and 'state management'.
    This is done to recognize valid tokens and recover from malformed input streams.

Language Subset Specifications
Specified Keywords has been implemented -> // Enum for keyword token types (int, char, if, else, while, for, do, return).
Specified Identifiers is yet to be implemented!
Specified Numeric Literals (int) has been implemented -> // Enum for identifier token type (0-9).
Specified Delimiters has been implemented -> // Enum for separator/ delimiter token types (;,,,(,),{,},[,]).

Complex Token Handling and Error Recovery is yet to be implemented!

Token Recognition seems to be implemented...

For each token, need to record exact string match and the token type.

